comment: I don’t know the full situation but I think whatever person did to another they should each follow up for. I also think that if Johnny depps career suffered but hers didn’t and she did similar things too I don’t find that fair. I think they should each be penalized for each offense according to the offense (but it shouldnt be more or less than the offense) it should match the offense. And probably vice versa But I also think messing with their careers isn’t really fair. I think on Jonny’s part if he did anything to her he should still be allowed to play roles and have his career back

comment: I'm signing due to new evidence that showed she did not donate the money which was not availble during the NGN trial. The NGN trial also had conflicts of interest since how can you say its okay for a judge to be in on the trial while his wife is on one of the people in the trial's team and the fact he also had dinner with Amber heard. What does this say about the morale of the judges since Nicol has made mistake rulings but this ruling made was a mistake since he did not believe one side witness despite them being police officers.  New evidence brought to light on how Judge Nicol ruled she isn't a gold digger since she said she donated has shown she has not even donated the full amount she said she was going to.  There is a difference between pledge and donate since the documents revealed she did not donate, her team modified the photos to show nothing to show abuse yet Johnny had to get his hand put in a cast from when she threw a glass bottle at his hand.  Judges get it wrong but this conflict of interest well if Murdoch wasn't involved if it wasn't his business  would the trial result be the same since there was no evidence that he abused her since the article written was done without any actual proof but rather written during the me too movement
